  "prompt": "How do I get into NYU journalism?",
  "response": "To get into NYU's journalism program, here are some key steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Take advanced English and writing courses in high school\n- Maintain a strong GPA (typically 3.5 or higher)\n- Take AP or honors classes if possible\n\n2. Standardized Testing\n- Submit competitive SAT/ACT scores\n- NYU's journalism programs typically look for scores around 1400+ on SAT\n\n3. Application Process\n- Apply through NYU's undergraduate admissions\n- Apply to the Steinhardt School of Culture, Education, and Human Development\n- Choose Media, Culture, and Communication major or Journalism concentration\n\n4. Strengthen Your Application\n- Write a compelling personal statement\n- Highlight writing achievements\n- Include journalism-related extracurricular activities\n- Submit writing samples\n- Get strong letters of recommendation\n\n5. Additional Recommendations\n- Participate in school newspaper\n- Start a blog or write for local publications\n- Take journalism workshops\n- Develop a strong portfolio of writing samples\n\n6. Consider Requirements\n- Check specific program requirements on NYU's official website\n- Attend information sessions\n- Consider campus visits\n\nEach application is evaluated holistically, so showcase your passion for journalism.",
